For An Act To Be Entitled
8
9 AN ACT TO REQUIRE A PUBLIC HIGH SCHOOL TO GRANT
10 ACCESS TO ITS FACILITIES TO OFFICIAL RECRUITING
11 REPRESENTATIVES OF THE MILITARY; TO REQUIRE CERTAIN
12 STATE-SUPPORTED POSTSECONDARY INSTITUTIONS TO GRANT
13 ACCESS TO ITS FACILITIES TO OFFICIAL RECRUITING
14 REPRESENTATIVES OF THE MILITARY; AND FOR OTHER
15 PURPOSES.
16
17
Subtitle
18
19 TO REQUIRE A PUBLIC HIGH SCHOOL TO GRANT
20 ACCESS TO ITS FACILITIES TO MILITARY
21 RECRUITERS; AND TO REQUIRE CERTAIN
22 STATE-SUPPORTED POSTSECONDARY
23 INSTITUTIONS TO GRANT ACCESS TO ITS
24 FACILITIES TO MILITARY RECRUITERS.
25
26 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
27
28 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code § 6-13-626 is amended to read as follows:
29 6-13-626. Access of military recruiters to school facilities and
30 records — Definitions.
31 (a) If the board of directors of a school district permits access to
32 the school grounds, facilities, and records by any person or group of persons
33 whose purpose is to make students aware of occupational and educational
34 options and opportunities, the A public school district board of directors
35 shall also permit such grant access on the same basis within each high school
36 in its district to official recruiting representatives of the military forces
