HB1689
1 (f) The Secretary of the Department of the Military shall:
2 (1) Collect information from Arkansas National Guard recruiters
3 regarding compliance with this section by public school districts; and
4 (2) Prepare and submit an annual compliance report to the
5 Secretary of the Department of Education based on information collected under
6 subdivision (f)(1) of this section that shall:
7 (A) Identify each public school district found to be in
8 violation of this section; and
9 (B) Explain the basis for determining a public school
10 district is in violation of this section.
11 (g)(1) Each public high school shall inform all students in grades ten
12 through twelve (10-12) of opportunities to receive direct military forces
13 recruiter engagement and information about educational and career
14 opportunities available in the military forces.
15 (2) The information required under subdivision (g)(1) of this
16 section shall be provided electronically and through a student advisory or
17 homeroom session or class period.
18 (h) As used in this section:
19 (1) "Access" means the ability of military forces recruiters to:
20 (A) Engage with all students in grades ten through twelve
21 (10-12) in an in-person setting during normal school hours and at events that
22 are open to the public and outside of normal school hours;
23 (B) Present career and educational opportunities to
24 students in the same manner and under the same conditions as prospective
25 employers, institutions of higher education, career entities, educational
26 entities, and occupational entities; and
27 (C) Collect and distribute information, sign up students
28 for further engagement, and schedule follow-up meetings to the same extent as
29 prospective employers, institutions of higher education, career entities,
30 educational entities, and occupational entities; and
31 (2) "Military forces" means the Arkansas National Guard, United
32 States Army, United States Marine Corps, United States Navy, United States
33 Air Force, United States Space Force, United States Coast Guard, and the
34 federal reserve components of each of the federal bodies.
35
36 SECTION 2. Arkansas Code Title 6, Chapter 50, Subchapter 1, is amended
3 03/05/2025 7:39:08 AM TNL161

HB1689
1 to add an additional section to read as follows:
2 6-50-107. Access of military forces recruiter to career and precollege
3 academies and secondary career and technical centers — Definition.
4 (a) A state-supported career academy, precollege academy, secondary
5 career center, or technical center shall permit access to official recruiting
6 representatives of the military forces to enable those representatives to
7 inform students enrolled in the state-supported career academy, precollege
8 academy, secondary career center, or technical center of educational and
9 career opportunities available in the military forces.
10 (b) As used in this section, "military forces" means the Arkansas
11 National Guard, United States Army, United States Marine Corps, United States
12 Navy, United States Air Force, United States Space Force, United States Coast
13 Guard, and the federal reserve components of each of the federal bodies.
14
15 SECTION 3. Arkansas Code Title 6, Chapter 61, Subchapter 1, is amended
16 to add an additional section to read as follows:
17 6-61-144. Access of military recruiter to postsecondary institution
18 facilities — Definition.
19 (a) A state-supported institution of higher education shall permit
20 access to official recruiting representatives of the military forces to
21 enable those representatives to inform students enrolled in the state-
22 supported institution of higher education of educational and career
23 opportunities available in the military.
24 (b) As used in this section, "military forces" means the Arkansas
25 National Guard, United States Army, United States Marine Corps, United States
26 Navy, United States Air Force, United States Space Force, United States Coast
27 Guard, and the federal reserve components of each of the federal bodies.
